service: This API reference provides descriptions, syntax, and other details about each of the actions and data types for AWS Migration Hub Orchestrator. he topic for each action shows the API request parameters and the response. Alternatively, you can use one of the AWS SDKs to access an API that is tailored to the programming language or platform that you're using.

operations.CreateWorkflow: Create a workflow to orchestrate your migrations.
operations.CreateWorkflowStep: Create a step in the migration workflow.
operations.CreateWorkflowStepGroup: Create a step group in a migration workflow.
operations.DeleteWorkflow: Delete a migration workflow. You must pause a running workflow in Migration Hub Orchestrator console to delete it.
operations.DeleteWorkflowStep: Delete a step in a migration workflow. Pause the workflow to delete a running step.
operations.DeleteWorkflowStepGroup: Delete a step group in a migration workflow.
operations.GetTemplate: Get the template you want to use for creating a migration workflow.
operations.GetTemplateStep: Get a specific step in a template.
operations.GetTemplateStepGroup: Get a step group in a template.
operations.GetWorkflowStep: Get a step in the migration workflow.
operations.GetWorkflowStepGroup: Get the step group of a migration workflow.
operations.ListTagsForResource: List the tags added to a resource.
operations.ListTemplateStepGroups: List the step groups in a template.
operations.ListTemplates: List the templates available in Migration Hub Orchestrator to create a migration workflow.
operations.ListWorkflowStepGroups: List the step groups in a migration workflow.
operations.RetryWorkflowStep: Retry a failed step in a migration workflow.
operations.TagResource: Tag a resource by specifying its Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
operations.UpdateWorkflowStep: Update a step in a migration workflow.
operations.UpdateWorkflowStepGroup: Update the step group in a migration workflow.
